    "dept": "AGRON",
    "num": "531",
    "desc": "Prereq: AGRON 501, AGRON 502, AGRON 503; AGRON 512 and AGRON 514 recommended\nEcological principles underlying crop production systems. Crop production in the context of management approaches, system resources and constraints, and interactions. Emphasis on the ecology of row and forage crops common to the Midwest. Required course for the Master of Science in Agronomy degree program.\n",
