    "dept": "COM S",
    "num": "631",
    "desc": "Prereq: COM S 531\nAdvanced study in the quantitative theory of computation. Time and space complexity of algorithmic problems. The structure of P, NP, PH, PSPACE, and other complexity classes, especially with respect to resource-bounded reducibilities and complete problems. Complexity relative to auxiliary information, including oracle computation and relativized classes, randomized algorithms, advice machines, Boolean circuits. Kolmogorov complexity and randomness.  Novel models of computation emerging in a rapidly changing field.\n",
