    "dept": "E E",
    "num": "576",
    "desc": "Prereq: E E 475 or AER E 432 or M E 411 or MATH 415; and MATH 267\nSampled data, discrete data, and the z-transform. Design of digital control systems using transform methods: root locus, frequency response and direct design methods. Design using state-space methods. Controllability, observability, pole placement, state estimators. Digital filters in control systems. Microcomputer implementation of digital filters. Finite wordlength effects. Linear quadratic optimal control in digital control systems. Simulation of digital control systems.\n",
    "credits": "3"
