    "course_name": "Fundamentals of Bioinformatics",
    "dept": "GDCB",
    "num": "544",
    "desc": "Prereq: MATH 165 or STAT 401 or equivalent\nA practical, hands-on overview of how to apply bioinformatics to biological research. Recommended for biologists desiring to gain computational molecular biology skills. Topics include: sequence analysis, genomics, proteomics, phylogenetic analyses, ontology enrichment, systems biology, data visualization and emergent technologies.\n",
