    "desc": "Prereq: GEOL 452, C R P 351, C R P 452, NREM 345, or NREM 446\nIntroduction to geospatial data collection, analysis, interpretation, and presentation. Geospatial techniques including geographic information systems (GIS), remote sensing (RS), and global positioning systems (GPS). Study of applied geostatistical analysis (e.g., interpolation and spatial regression).\n",
