    "dept": "L A",
    "num": "594",
    "desc": "Prereq: Graduate standing or senior classification.\nExamination of the equitable distribution of environmental burdens and benefits for sustainable and resilient cities. Focus on impact of climate change, social exclusion, and physical isolation on cumulative risk amongst vulnerable populations. Synthesis of recent social and environmental research to develop innovative physical planning and urban design strategies that support healthy behaviors.\n",
