    "dept": "STAT",
    "num": "510",
    "desc": "Prereq: STAT 500, STAT 447 or credit/enrollment in STAT 543\nLinear models and analysis of variance for multifactor experiments with balanced and unbalanced data. Likelihood analysis for general linear models and models with non-normal random components; linear model results in the context of likelihood; linear mixed models and their application; estimation, inference, and prediction. Introduction to generalized linear models and generalized linear mixed models. Case studies of applications including problem formulation, exploratory analysis, model development, estimation and inference, and model assessment.\n",
